<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="101" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo elliotii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliotii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Paramollugo elliotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Lam." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Paramollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo simulans" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Paramollugo simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by perennial life form, narrow (linear to oblanceolate), (sub)sessile leaves, larger anthers (0.55-0.70 mm), and larger outer perianth segments (2.6-3 mm) at the fruiting stage (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Lam." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo nudicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudicaulis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Paramollugo nudicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo simulans" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Paramollugo simulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are annuals, with broader, usually petiolate leaves, anthers of 0.25-0.30 mm and smaller perianth to 2.4 mm long).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
