</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="101" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="101">
All except one specimen are nearly a hundred years old or even older, and no information is available on the current extent of the wild populations of this species. Therefore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukhor" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Paramollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Paramollugo elliotii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="8" pageNumber="101" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elliotii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="101">Paramollugo elliotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given a Data Deficient (DD) status (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee" pageId="11" pageNumber="104" publicationUrl="http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B11" refString="IUCN, 2016. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List categories and criteria. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf [accessed 10.08.2016]" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List categories and criteria" url="http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2016">IUCN 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="102" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="102">
<pageBreakToken pageId="9" pageNumber="102" start="start">Etymology</pageBreakToken>
